          "id": "47cdeb01abe5330797cee26fb014abcc69ad9714",
          "message": "fix(mise): minimum age does not cause pinned versions to fail (#575)\n\n* docs: add comment explaining version availability check rationale\n\nGenerated-by: aiautocommit\n\n* feat: add test example for python and uv latest with min age requirement\n\nGenerated-by: aiautocommit\n\n* feat: update test project dependencies in mise task\n\n* Automate upgrading the dependencies for the Python example project during the mise-upgrade task.\n* Ensure the repository remains current with the latest versions during the automated maintenance flow.\n\nGenerated-by: aiautocommit\n\n* fix(mise): support pinned versions and minimum_release_age\n\n* test(core): add snapshot for python-uv-latest-locked build plan\n\nGenerated-by: aiautocommit\n\n* docs: mise locked edge version test\n\n* refactor(mise): remove hardcoded minimum release age\n\n- Remove the hardcoded MISE_MINIMUM_RELEASE_AGE environment variable to allow configuration via system defaults or user settings.\n\nGenerated-by: aiautocommit\n\n* test(node): verify latest node version in tests\n\n- Update the node version expectation to accept any valid version string when configured as \"latest\".\n- This avoids brittle test failures caused by the actual \"latest\" version changing over time.\n\nGenerated-by: aiautocommit",
