          "id": "8bf1cbf4b3cd5cf97aa1dc69cfbbede4b1b20545",
          "message": "feat(node): add support for Expo SPA builds (#585)\n\n* feat(expo-spa): scaffold initial expo spa project structure\n\n*   Initialize core directory structure for expo-spa example.\n*   Add theme management hooks and components to handle color schemes.\n*   Include necessary assets for branding and UI components.\n*   Setup initial configuration files and root layout.\n\nGenerated-by: aiautocommit\n\n* feat(node): add support for Expo SPA builds\n\n- Detect Expo projects using 'expo' and 'react-native-web' dependencies with static web output configured in 'app.json'.\n- Automatically add a build command for 'expo export --platform web' when no build script is defined.\n- Configure output directory resolution and runtime categorization for Expo applications.\n\nGenerated-by: aiautocommit\n\n* docs: update documentation for Expo Web support and SPA build process\n\nGenerated-by: aiautocommit\n\n* refactor(expo): remove default expo export command\n\n- Remove the hardcoded Expo CLI export command.\n- Rely on projects defining their own build scripts to maintain flexibility and alignment with standard Node provider patterns.\n\nGenerated-by: aiautocommit\n\n* feat(expo): support static and single web output modes\n\n- Update detection logic to include \"single\" output mode as a valid configuration for Expo SPAs.\n- Add case-insensitive comparison for web output mode to ensure robustness.\n\nGenerated-by: aiautocommit\n\n* test: add build plan snapshot for expo-spa project\n\nGenerated-by: aiautocommit\n\n* docs: update Expo Web SPA mode detection criteria\n\nGenerated-by: aiautocommit",
          "timestamp": "2026-06-17T19:47:43Z",
